criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age > 18years and < 80years;

          -  Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease Gold III-IV;

          -  Stable (no exacerbation) in the past 4 weeks;

          -  Referred for pulmonary rehabilitation (no cardiac, neurological, orthopedic,
             neuromuscular, psychological or psychiatric contra indication).

        Non-inclusion Criteria:

          -  Acute exacerbation of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease between the incremental
             cardiopulmonary exercise testing and inclusion;

          -  Tracheostomy;

          -  Nasal high flow intolerance;

          -  Pregnancy or likely to be;

          -  Unable to consent;

          -  Patients under guardianship.
